<p>I had an invited talk at the</p>

<p class="text-center fs-6"><a href="https://www.bradu.eu/2021/12/15/invited-talk-at-advances-in-3om/">1st International Conference Advances in 3OM: Opto-Mechatronics, Opto-Mechanics and Optical Metrology</a></p>

<p>on Combining Photoacoustic and Optical Coherence Tomography Imaging for non-destructive applications. Soon, an SPIE Proceedings on combining these two technologies are going to be published. A link will be posted here. Thanks the organisers for inviting me!</p>

<p class="label label-yellow">Link for proceedings:</p>

<p>Gianni Nteroli, Adrian Podoleanu, and <strong>Adrian Bradu</strong>, “<a href="https://doi.org/10.1117/12.2626041">Combining photoacoustic and optical coherence tomography imaging for nondestructive testing applications</a>,” Proc. SPIE, <strong>12170</strong>, Advances in 3OM: Opto-Mechatronics, Opto-Mechanics, and Optical Metrology; 121700P (2022).</p>

